GF(2^255-19) field arithmetic on the 10-limb 26/25-bit representation,
the make-or-break brick of X25519 (per docs/x25519-design.md). A field
element is 10 signed-i64 limbs with alternating 26/25-bit widths, kept
non-negative and fully reduced (invariant I1).

fadd(a, b): limb-wise add then carry-reduce.
fsub(a, b): a + 2p - b (biased to stay non-negative) then reduce.
fmul(a, b): schoolbook 10x10 with odd*odd doubling and the 2^255 = 19
            fold, then two carry passes. Every accumulator stays below
            2^59, so no high-half multiply is ever needed.

Each rule takes two elements (20 limbs) + which output limb (0..9).
Validated against big-int (a op b) mod (2^255-19) over 20000 random
vectors and edge cases.
